Validus Said U.S. Storms in April, May Cost Up to $75 Million

-- B y   B r o o k e   S u t h e r l a n d
-- 
2011-06-23T20:15:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-23/validus-said-u-s-storms-in-april-may-cost-up-to-75-million.html
Validus Holdings Ltd. (VR) , the reinsurer
that bought IPC Holdings Ltd., said U.S. storms in April and May
cost the company as much as $75 million.  The storms probably cost at least $55 million, the
Bermuda-based insurer said today in a statement distributed by
 Business Wire .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Brooke Sutherland in New York at 
 bsutherland5@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Kraut at 
 dkraut2@bloomberg.net  